defaultDiversity of providers and mdefaultodelsdefault&#xa0;
defaultA healthy public service market stipulates that the state 
defaultshould 
defaultno longer be the default provider. We have worked hard to introduce a number of different models in contracting with the private, public, voluntary and social enterprise sectors.
defaultPayment by results
defaultPayment by r
defaultesults focuses the attention of services and service providers on outcomes that matter for citizens, rather than on targets for inpu
defaultts or activity. In doing so, payment by results
default schemes offer the prospect of flexible providers tailoring services to user needs, spurring innovation and ensuring that government only rewards success.
defaultPayment by r
defaultesults is increasingly a core part of many public services including health, employment, drug recovery, housing, immigration and services for troubled families; and new pilots have been launched in debt collection, international development and psychological therapies. 
defaultT
defaulthe Government has introduced payment by results
default to a wide range of public services. Thes
defaulte services deploy a range of payment by results
default models and are at very different stages of development.
